p: At the larval stage, all tested compounds at 52 ppm, except cedrelanolide, inhibited growth. At lower concentrations, only compounds 177a and 178a showed higher insecticidal activity, with 83.3% larval mortality at 10 ppm. After 21 days, it was observed that compound 181 showed better results than the positive control, toosendanin, at 5 ppm.
